nce","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedFloat32Array","isActive":true},{"text":" for a more memory-friendly alternative.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Differences between packed arrays, typed arrays, and untyped arrays:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Packed arrays are generally faster to iterate on and modify compared to a typed array of the same type (e.g. ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedFloat64Array","isActive":true},{"text":" versus ","type":"text"},{"code":"Arrayfloat","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"). Also, packed arrays consume less memory. As a downside, packed arrays are less flexible as they don’t offer as many convenience methods such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Array\/map(method:)"},{"text":". Typed arrays are in turn faster to iterate on and modify than untyped arrays.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Packed arrays are always passed by reference. To get a copy of an array that can be modified independently of the original array, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/PackedFloat64Array\/duplicate()","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". This is "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"not"}]},{"type":"text","text":" the case for built-in properties and methods. The returned packed array of these are a copies, and changing it will "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"not","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" affect the original value. To update a built-in property you need to modify the returned array, and then assign it to the property again."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","t